# Dhruv Ghosh Personal Portfolio - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
This is a modern, animated single-page portfolio website built with Next.js 14, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and Framer Motion.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Framer Motion for animations
- Google Fonts (Clash Display, Satoshi)

## Design System

### Colors
- Primary: White (#FFFFFF, #FAFAFA)
- Secondary: Royal Green (#1B5E20, #2E7D32)
- Accent: Gold (#D4AF37, #FFD700)
- Text: Dark charcoal (#1A1A1A)

### Typography
- Headings: Clash Display (bold, distinctive)
- Body: Satoshi (clean, modern)

## Code Style Guidelines

### General
- Use TypeScript for all files
- Prefer functional components with hooks
- Use named exports for components
- Keep components focused and single-responsibility

### File Organization
- Components in `/components`
- Reusable UI components in `/components/ui`
- Data/content in `/lib/data.ts`
- Styles in `/app/globals.css` and Tailwind classes

### Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `Hero.tsx`)
- Utilities: camelCase (e.g., `formatDate.ts`)
- CSS variables: kebab-case with `--` prefix

### Animation Guidelines
- Use Framer Motion for scroll-triggered animations
- Implement parallax effects for visual depth
- Add hover states with smooth transitions
- Use stagger animations for lists/grids
- Keep animations performant (prefer transform/opacity)

### Tailwind Usage
- Use custom CSS variables for theme colors
- Prefer Tailwind utilities over custom CSS
- Use responsive prefixes consistently (sm:, md:, lg:, xl:)
- Group related utilities logically

### Component Structure
```tsx
'use client'; // if using hooks/interactivity

import { motion } from 'framer-motion';
// other imports

interface ComponentProps {
  // typed props
}

export function Component({ prop }: ComponentProps) {
  // hooks first
  // handlers
  // render
}
```

### Performance
- Use Next.js Image component for images
- Lazy load below-fold content
- Optimize animations for 60fps
- Minimize bundle size

### Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Include proper ARIA labels
- Ensure keyboard navigation
- Maintain color contrast ratios

## Git Workflow
- Commit messages: descriptive and concise
- Branch naming: feature/description or fix/description

